RESULT: The red “Inverted Cables” LED has 0.0 V at its anode and 11.9893 V at its cathode, so there is essentially the full 12 V across it in reverse direction. The series resistor shows 11.9893 V on both ends, indicating no voltage drop across the resistor itself.
